Joseph H. PRIMAKOW and Walter C. Rawles, Plaintiffs in Error, v. William C. HECHT, as United States Marshal, etc., Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 20, 1925. No. 235. B. P. Siegelstein, of New York City, for appellants. William Hayward, TJ. S. Atty., of New York City (Moses Polakoff, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), opposed.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order (7 F.[2d] 133) affirmed.
